================================================================================
DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

"norxs" means norxs Technology LLC, a Wyoming limited liability company.

"SOFTWARE" means the zonal-zero-trust-authenticator source code, documentation,
build scripts, CI configuration, and all associated files published under this
license. The SOFTWARE implements a Zero-Trust SPDM authentication engine for
Zonal ECUs over SOME/IP, including the CryptoPlatformInterface Platform
Abstraction Layer, SpdmProtocolEngine finite state machine, and
TokenLifecycleManager session governance engine.

"REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION" means a functional, standards-compliant demonstration
of norxs engineering capability intended for evaluation, education, and
competitive differentiation purposes only.

"COMMERCIAL USE" means any use of the SOFTWARE, or a substantial portion thereof,
in a product, service, or system that is sold, licensed, leased, or otherwise
transferred to a third party for commercial gain, including integration into
automotive ECUs, gateways, controllers, or software platforms deployed in
production vehicles or vehicle development programs.

"DERIVATIVE WORK" means any work that incorporates, modifies, translates, adapts,
or is otherwise based upon the SOFTWARE or any portion thereof.

